hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a function $f: [0, \pi] \to \mathbb{R}$ defined such that for any $x$ in the interval $[0, \pi]$, its value is given by:
$$
f(x) = \begin{cases} 
\sin(x)  \text{if } x \in \mathbb{Q} \\
0  \text{if } x \notin \mathbb{Q} 
\end{cases}
$$
where $\mathbb{Q}$ represents the set of rational numbers.

Let $L(f)$ and $U(f)$ denote the lower and upper Riemann integrals of the function $f$ over the interval $[0, \pi]$, respectively. Determine the values of $L(f)$ and $U(f)$. Report your answer as a row matrix containing two entries, where the first entry is the value of $L(f)$ and the second entry is the value of $U(f)$.
